verbose_text: Secondary objectives included the effect of a herbal formulation containing pycnogenol, papain and A. vera as the principle actives in the supplement compared to placebo on : (i) the proportion of patients with IGT; (ii) hs-CRP level (iii) changes in HbA1c; (iv) safety (liver function, urea and full blood count); (v) HDL, LDL, TGs and lipid profile; vi) quality of life (SF12v2 questionnaire).
